problems.statement:
Let x₁, ..., xₖ ∈ ℝⁿ. Define

C = {∑ᵢ₌₁ᵏ θᵢxᵢ | θᵢ ≥ 0, ∑ᵢ₌₁ᵏ θᵢ = 1}

Show that C is convex.

For S ⊂ ℝⁿ, let conv(S) be its convex hull (all finite convex combinations of points in S). Show:

conv(S) = ⋂ {C ⊂ ℝⁿ | C is convex and S ⊆ C}

In words: the convex hull of S is the intersection of all convex sets containing S.
